SUMMARY:"A Good Deal" at the Cloverdale Performing Arts Center
DESCRIPTION:By Ron Nash\nDirector Jenna Dolcini \nA Raven on the Road Production at the Cloverdale Performing Arts Center \nKate\, a psychologist from Santa Fe\, unexpectedly shows up at the door of her old flame\, Bo\, with a life-changing secret she is reluctant to share. As she struggles with opening up to Bo\, Kate also seeks to reconnect with her estranged daughter who lives nearby. Brimming with humanity and humor\, A Good Deal is a bittersweet tale of love\, loss\, and family connections. Developed through the Raven Players’ ScripTease program. \nFebruary 27th\, 28th\, March 1st\, 6th\, 7th\, 8th. \nFriday and Saturday Shows: 7:30 PM\nSunday Matinee: 2:00 PM\nDoors open 30 minutes before showtime. \nAdults: $25\nStudent w/ID: $10
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/a-good-deal-at-the-cloverdale-performing-arts-center-3/
LOCATION:Cloverdale Performing Arts Center\, 209 N. Cloverdale Blvd.\, Cloverdale\, CA
CATEGORIES:Theater
