SUMMARY:SOLD OUT-Mushroom Hike at Sugarloaf Park
DESCRIPTION:Explore the hidden world beneath our feet on this mushroom hike led by local mycologist George Riner. We’ll observe their growth\, learn to identify different species by key traits\, be mesmerized by the display of colors\, shapes\, textures\, and discuss these remarkable organisms’ ecological roles\, culinary delights\, and even a touch of folklore. \nBe prepared for two miles of leisurely walking and chatting over moderate and possibly muddy terrain. Please be aware this is not a foray; collection is permitted for this activity through a yearly CA State Parks Scientific Research and Collecting permit. Fungi information is for educational purposes only. Foraging is illegal in CA State Parks. \nYou must purchase a ticket through this page to attend. Tickets are $10 for general audiences\, $5 for students\, youth (12-17 years old; children under 18 years old must be accompanied by a parent or guardian)\, Sugarloaf members\, Sugarloaf and RFO volunteers\, and free for children under 12. Meet outside the Visitor Center ten minutes prior to the event start time. \nWear layers and appropriate footwear for muddy/slippery trails\, bring at least a quart of water\, and if you have them\, mushroom identifying guides. We invite you to bring a reusable drink container so your little ones can enjoy hot cocoa after the walk\, if desired. Heavy rain cancels; parking fees apply. Parking fees apply.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/mushroom-hike-at-sugarloaf-park-2/
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA
CATEGORIES:Recreation
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Mushroom-hike-Sugarloaf-s.jpg
GEO:38.4427;-122.533
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Sugarloaf Ridge State Park 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd Kenwood CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=2605 Adobe Canyon Rd:geo:-122.533,38.4427
END:VEVENT
